ZCZC GE63
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SATURDAY TO TUESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 022300 UTC
DURING SATURDAY EVENING AND SUNDAY A COMPLEX LOW PRESSURE AREA IN THE NORWEGIAN
SEA AND N SEA WILL MIGRATE EWARDS AS A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE BUILDS ACROSS
THE UK. A DEEP AREA OF LOW PRESSURE 957 WILL DEVELOP TO THE SW OF ICELAND
LATER WITH AN ASSOCIATED FRONTAL TROUGH APPROACHING THE BRITISH ISLES. THIS
VERY ACTIVE FRONTAL TROUGH WILL MOV TO LIE OVER SCOTLAND AND IRELAND THROUGH
MONDAY. THIS TROUGH WILL RELAX NEWARDS LATER TUESDAY LEAVING A COMPLEX AREA
OF LOW PRESSURE BETWEEN SCOTLAND AND ICELAND AND A CYCLONIC PRESSURE PATTERN
ACROSS MOST SEA AREAS. OCNL STRG WINDS ARE FCST ON SATURDAY EVENING AND SUNDAY
IN ALL SEA AREAS WITH POSS GALES IN THE N LATER SUNDAY. WINDS WILL MOD FOR
A TIME ON MONDAY BUT STRG TO GALE SW WINDS WILL DEVELOP LATER MONDAY AND
TUESDAY IN THE N SEA AND THAMES DOVER AND WIGHT ON TUESDAY. SEV GALES OR
STORMS ARE POSS IN N ON TUESDAY
